Que 1) Notification System using Spring Core and Factory Pattern
=================================================================

Problem Statement:
You are developing a Notification System for an application that needs to send messages to users through different communication channels.
The system supports the following notification types:
Email
SMS
Push Notification

Each notification type has its own implementation for sending messages, but all follow a common interface.
To ensure loose coupling and scalability, you must use:
Spring Core (Annotation-based configuration)
Factory Design Pattern with Map-based Dependency Injection
The system should dynamically select and use the appropriate notification service at runtime based on user input.

Requirements:
===============

1️) Create an interface Notification
Method:
String sendNotification(String message);

2️) Create implementation classes:
EmailNotification
SMSNotification
PushNotification
Conditions:
Each class must implement Notification
Each class must be annotated with @Component
Use the following component names:
"email"
"sms"
"push"
Behavior:
Email → return "Email sent: <message>"
SMS → return "SMS sent: <message>"
Push → return "Push notification sent: <message>"

3️) Create a Factory class NotificationFactory
Conditions:
Annotate the class with @Component
Use Map-based Dependency Injection
@Autowired
private Map<String, Notification> notificationMap;

Method:
public Notification getNotification(String type)
Logic:
Convert input type to lowercase
Retrieve object from notificationMap
If object is not found → throw IllegalArgumentException("Invalid Notification Type")
Return the corresponding Notification object

4️) Create Configuration class
Annotate with:
@Configuration
@ComponentScan(basePackages = "your package name")

5️) Create Main Class (ELC)

Class Name: NotificationApp

Responsibilities:
Load Spring container using AnnotationConfigApplicationContext
Get NotificationFactory bean
Take input from user:
Notification type
Message
Call getNotification(type)
Call sendNotification(message)
Handle exception for invalid input

Sample Input/Output:
-------------------------
Enter notification type: sms
Enter message: Hello User
SMS sent: Hello User

